icationHeading\">Alerts In Effect</h2>\n<button aria-label=\"Dismiss\" class=\"AlertsNotification__DismissButton\" type=\"button\">\nDismiss\n<svg class=\"usa-icon\" focusable=\"false\" role=\"presentation\">\n<use href=\"/theme/assets/vendor/npsds/packages/icons/dist/sprite.svg#close\"></use>\n</svg>\n</button>\n<span class=\"hr clearfix\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__Body\" id=\"AlertsNotificationBody\">\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__MoreLinkContainer\">\n<svg class=\"usa-icon\" focusable=\"false\" role=\"presentation\">\n<use href=\"/theme/assets/vendor/npsds/packages/icons/dist/sprite.svg#add\"></use>\n</svg>\n<a class=\"AlertsNotification__MoreLink\" href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/conditions.htm\" id=\"AlertsNotificationMoreLink\" tabindex=\"-1\">\nmore information on current conditions...\n</a>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"MainContent\" id=\"main\" role=\"main\">\n\n<div aria-labelledby=\"modal-contact-us-label\" class=\"modal fade\" id=\"modal-contact-us\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n<div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n<div class=\"modal-content\">\n<div class=\"modal-header\">\n<h4 class=\"modal-title visually-hidden\" id=\"modal-contact-us-label\">Contact Us</h4>\n<button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"btn-close\" data-bs-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"></button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"modal-body\">\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"adminTools\"></div>\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"ColumnGrid row\">\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n<div class=\"container\">\n\n</div>\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<div class=\"ColumnMain col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"ContentHeader text-content-size\">\n<h1 class=\"page-title\">Geology for Students</h1>\n</div>\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Layout\" id=\"cs_control_2\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"CS_Layout_Table\" id=\"cs_idLayout2\" summary=\"\" width=\"100%\"><tr class=\"CS_Layout_TR\"><td class=\"CS_Layout_TD\" id=\"cs_idCell2x1x1\">\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_6801998\">\n\n</div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_6779713\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_6779713\">\n<div class=\"ImportantLinks\">\n<div class=\"row mb-5\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-6 col-md-4 col-lg-3 order-sm-last\">\n\n</div>\n<div class=\"col-sm-6 col-md-8 col-lg-9\">\n<h2>Geology: Studying the Story of Rocks\n </h2>\n<p>Imagine a canyon of rock one mile deep, up to 18 miles wide, and 277 miles long. That is a big slice through the ground! Grand Canyon displays more than 20 layers of rocks, and each layer is like a page in Earth's history book. <strong>Geology</strong>, the study of Earth, helps tell the story of rocks.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_7011639\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_7011639\"> \n\n<div class=\"gallery-listing-av webcam-gallery responsiveVideoLinkNoHighlights\">\n<ul class=\"gallery-content-av clearfix\">\n<li>\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-md-3 col-sm-3 col-xs-12\">\n<div class=\"image\">\n<a class=\"cc\" href=\"/media/video/view.htm?id=1E178A20-AFD5-4939-AE93-4B364C2AC771\">\n<div style=\"background: url('/common/uploads/imr/park/grca//546AA637-0C80-182F-137E54BD453EB4B2/546AA637-0C80-182F-137E54BD453EB4B2-thumbnail.jpg') center center black;\">\n<img alt=\"Grand Canyon Geology Write Out \" border=\"0\" class=\"avArea-thumb\" src=\"/common/commonspot/templates/images/buttons/thumb_play_button.png\"/>\n</div>\n</a>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"col-md-9 col-sm-9 col-xs-12 avItem\">\n<div class=\"avDescription clearfix\">\n<h3><a class=\"cc\" href=\"/media/video/view.htm?id=1E178A20-AFD5-4939-AE93-4B364C2AC771\">Grand Canyon Geology Write Out </a></h3>\n<p>Have you ever wondered why Grand Canyon is so colorful? Learn about fossils, rocks and scale at Grand Canyon National Park, in celebration of Write Out, a national writing campaign —then get outside and reflect on change in your community. Imagine yourself standing on the landscape one million years in the future. Create a postcard depicting what you see. On the back, write a letter describing your experience. Use the hashtag #WriteOut if you'd like to share your work with others.\n</p>\n<dl class=\"result-details wrapped\">\n<dt>Duration:</dt><dd>4 minutes, 42 seconds</dd>\n</dl>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_6803629\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_6803629\">\n\n<div class=\"gallery-listing-av webcam-gallery responsiveVideoLinkNoHighlights\">\n<ul class=\"gallery-content-av clearfix\">\n<li>\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-md-3 col-sm-3 col-xs-12\">\n<div class=\"image\">\n<a class=\"cc\" href=\"/media/video/view.htm?id=28F9B171-155D-451F-67F026D7D0DBFD87\">\n<div style=\"background: url('https://www.nps.gov/nps-audiovideo/legacy/grca/28F9B171-155D-451F-67F026D7D0DBFD87/grca-fly-over-720_thumb.jpg') center center black;\">\n<img alt=\"Grand Canyon Fly-through Animation\" border=\"0\" class=\"avArea-thumb\" src=\"/common/commonspot/templates/images/buttons/thumb_play_button.png\"/>\n</div>\n</a>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"col-md-9 col-sm-9 col-xs-12 avItem\">\n<div class=\"avDescription clearfix\">\n<h3><a class=\"cc\" href=\"/media/video/view.htm?id=28F9B171-155D-451F-67F026D7D0DBFD87\">Grand Canyon Fly-through Animation</a></h3>\n<p>Experience roller-coaster twists and turns flying the length of the Colorado River while listening to a narrated introduction to Grand Canyon Geography.</p>\n<dl class=\"result-details wrapped\">\n<dt>Duration:</dt><dd>7 minutes, 19 seconds</dd>\n</dl>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_6779689\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_6779689\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<figure class=\"-right\">\n<picture>\n<source srcset=\"/grca/learn/nature/images/figure1_3.png?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false&amp;quality=78&amp;format=webp\" type=\"image/webp\"/>\n<img alt=\"Outlined drawing, labeling the layers of Grand Canyon\" src=\"/grca/learn/nature/images/figure1_3.png?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false\" title=\"\"/>\n</picture>\n</figure><!-- floating-image alignment  -->\n<h2>Grand Canyon's Rock Layers</h2>\n<p>What does Grand Canyon have in common with pancakes? The oldest layers, which formed first, are usually at the bottom, while the younger layers are stacked on top.<br/>\n<br/>\n<strong>Sedimentary</strong> rocks form the middle and top layers of Grand Canyon. Layers of sediment hardened into sedimentary rocks over time.<br/>\n<br/>\nMost of the canyon's igneous and metamorphic rocks make up the bottom layers of Grand Canyon, near the Colorado River. <strong>Igneous</strong> rocks formed when liquid magma cooled. <strong>Metamorphic</strong> rocks formed when heat and pressure changed igneous, sedimentary, and other metamorphic rocks.<br/>\n<br/>\nOne of Grand Canyon's oldest rocks, Vishnu schist, is about 1.8 billion years old, more than one-third the age of Earth!<br/>\n<br/>\nTo explore more, navigate through an <a href=\"https://rclark.github.io/grand-canyon-geology/#10/36.2793/-112.2167\" id=\"https://rclark.github.io/grand-canyon-geology/#10/36.2793/-112.2167|\">interactive map of Grand Canyon's rock layers.</a></p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_6822589\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_6822589\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<figure class=\"-auto-width\">\n<picture>\n<source srcset=\"/grca/planyourvisit/images/fossils-3.jpg?maxwidth=1300&amp;autorotate=false&amp;quality=78&amp;format=webp\" type=\"image/webp\"/>\n<img alt=\"three fossils against a gray background. from left to right: a trilobite on green rock, fossil fern on rust-colored rock, a clam-like shell on white rock\" src=\"/grca/planyourvisit/images/fossils-3.jpg?maxwidth=1300&amp;autorotate=false\" title=\"Grand Canyon National Park Fossils\"/>\n</picture>\n<figcaption><p class=\"figcredit\">NPS Photo</p></figcaption>\n</figure><!-- floating-image alignment  -->\n<h2>Fossils Tell Stories of Ancient Life</h2>\n<p>Many rock layers in Grand Canyon contain fossils. Fossils give scientists clues about Earth's past environments and the animals and plants that lived in them.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_6868564\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_6868564\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<figure class=\"-right\">\n<a href=\"https://www.grandcanyon.org/classes-tours/youth-programs/cfs-home/geology/\">\n<picture>\n<source srcset=\"/grca/learn/education/images/cfs-geology_fa.gif\" type=\"image/gif\"/>\n<img alt=\"Series of graphics advertising various geology programs are in rotation and crafted in watercolor paint.\" src=\"/grca/learn/education/images/cfs-geology_fa.gif\" title=\"CFS Geology GIF\"/>\n</picture>\n</a>\n<figcaption>Explore more about geology through Canyon Field School @Home activities! </figcaption>\n</figure><!-- floating-image alignment  -->\n<h3>How Fossils Form</h3>\n<p>Fossils often form in sedimentary rocks. When layers of sediment hardened into rock, they sometimes trap the remains of animals and plants that have died. Over millions of years, these bones, shells, footprints, leaves and other remains turned into stone.</p>\n<h3>Stories in Stone</h3>\n<p>By studying fossils and comparing them to similar animals and plants that live today, scientists can find out what the environment was like before the canyon was carved.<br/>\n<br/>\nNot all of Grand Canyon's fossils have been found in rock. Some fossils from the Ice Age have been discovered in caves, where animals and plant remains dried out and preserved over time.<br/>\n<br/>\nLearn more about <a href=\"https://www.grandcanyon.org/classes-tours/youth-programs/cfs-home/geology/\" id=\"https://www.grandcanyon.org/classes-tours/youth-programs/cfs-home/geology/|\">Grand Canyon geology through Canyon Field School @Home activities</a>, partnered with the Grand Canyon Conservancy!</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_6780135\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_6780135\">\n\n<div class=\"gallery-listing-av webcam-gallery responsiveVideoLinkNoHighlights\">\n<ul class=\"gallery-content-av clearfix\">\n<li>\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-md-3 col-sm-3 col-xs-12\">\n<div class=\"image\">\n<a class=\"cc\" href=\"/media/video/view.htm?id=525CDC2A-DD6D-065F-DA682D34AB79CFD9\">\n<div style=\"background: url('/common/uploads/imr/park/grca/C31ED37F-C704-6483-DE6F7A96853C46FD/C31ED37F-C704-6483-DE6F7A96853C46FD-thumbnail.jpg') center center black;\">\n<img alt=\"Canyon Field School: Geology Video\" border=\"0\" class=\"avArea-thumb\" src=\"/common/commonspot/templates/images/buttons/thumb_play_button.png\"/>\n</div>\n</a>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"col-md-9 col-sm-9 col-xs-12 avItem\">\n<div class=\"avDescription clearfix\">\n<h3><a class=\"cc\" href=\"/media/video/view.htm?id=525CDC2A-DD6D-065F-DA682D34AB79CFD9\">Canyon Field School: Geology Video</a></h3>\n<p>An introduction to the ancient environments, fossils, geologic timelines, and rock layers of Grand Canyon.</p>\n<dl class=\"result-details wrapped\">\n<dt>Duration:</dt><dd>5 minutes, 50 seconds</dd>\n</dl>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_6823138\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_6823138\">\n\n<div class=\"container ListingList ListingResults\" id=\"searchListing-4AB0F24F-A480-E577-ACEA9AEDA41896E8\">\n<h2>Classroom Activities</h2>\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"results\">\n<a name=\"results\"></a>\n<div class=\"display-list-view\" id=\"display-list-view\">\n<div class=\"info-micro-filter\" style=\"display:none;\">\n<div class=\"result-count\"></div>\n<div class=\"result-selectors\">\n<div class=\"result-facet-Parks_Item result-facet-select\" data-facetfield=\"Parks_Item\" data-facettitle=\"Location\" style=\"display:none;\">\n<form action=\"#\" class=\"micro-filter facet-parks\">\n<span class=\"visually-hidden\">\n<label for=\"sort-by-select-searchListing-4AB0F24F-A480-E577-ACEA9AEDA41896E8\">Narrow By Location:</label>\n</span>\n<select multiple=\"\" name=\"result-narrow-Parks_Item\"></select>\n</form>\n</div>\n<div class=\"result-facet-Organizations_Item result-facet-select\" data-facetfield=\"Organizations_Item\" data-facettitle=\"Office\" style=\"display:none;\">\n<form action=\"#\" class=\"micro-filter facet-organizations\">\n<span class=\"visually-hidden\">\n<label for=\"sort-by-select-searchListing-4AB0F24F-A480-E577-ACEA9AEDA41896E8\">Narrow By Office:</label>\n</span>\n<select multiple=\"\" name=\"result-narrow-Organizations_Item\"></select>\n</form>\n</div>\n<div class=\"result-count-select\">\n<form action=\"#\" class=\"sort-by\" id=\"result-count-form\"><p><label for=\"result-count-select-searchListing-4AB0F24F-A480-E577-ACEA9AEDA41896E8\">Show</label><select id=\"result-count-select-searchListing-4AB0F24F-A480-E577-ACEA9AEDA41896E8\" name=\"result-maxRows\">\n<option value=\"10\">10</option>\n<option value=\"40\">40</option>\n</select></p></form>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><!--display-list-view-->\n<div class=\"FilterTags\" style=\"display:none;\"></div>\n<div class=\"ListingResults-loading\">\nLoadin